# POWER-THEME Project Rules

## Trading Strategy: A+ Elite Rubric
- Momentum must reflect a Stage 2 uptrend.
- EMA stack must be strictly ordered: price > 10EMA > 20EMA > 50EMA > 200EMA.
- Liquidity requirement: average daily dollar volume > $100M.
- Volatility requirement: ADR (Average Daily Range) > 4.5%.
- Market cap requirement: minimum $2B.

## Tech Stack Constraints
- Frontend must use React (Vite), Tailwind CSS, Lucide-React, and Recharts.
- Backend must use Python 3.11+, FastAPI, Uvicorn, BeautifulSoup4, and yfinance.
- All API endpoints must be asynchronous.
- Keep scraping/parsing logic separate from API route handlers.
- Prefer modular architecture with clear boundaries between data, logic, and transport layers.

## UI and Dashboard Direction
- Use an ultra-dark Quant aesthetic.
- Primary background baseline: Slate-950 (#020617).
- Dashboard logic must rank industries by Relative Strength (RS).
- Emphasize pure-play thematic clusters over broad mixed buckets.

## Coding Standards
- Use functional React components with Tailwind utility classes.
- Keep components and backend modules focused and composable.
- Favor explicit, readable implementations over implicit magic.
